"On tap at an Italian chain restaurant. Comes to the table a clear straw yellow color with a decent off white head that leaves spotty lacing. Smells of grainy malt a light floral hops. The flavor is as lackluster as the aroma. Light body with a moderate level of carbonation and a sweet grainy mouthfeel. Barely better than a Bud, but technically defect free, unless you consider a lack of flavor a flaw."
